node.text:
A hidden world of Chinese art 🇨🇳✨Have you heard of the Longmen grottoes before? This UNESCO World Heritage site in Luoyang, China contains the largest collection of Chinese art of the Northern Wei and Tang Dynasties. 

Insider tip: The grottoes are 13km south of Luoyang, and you can easily reach them by bus or taxi. After you've seen the west side, you can get a riverside view by taking the boat back to the main entrance (but don’t forget that you won’t be able to re-enter the west side after leaving).

📍 Luoyang, Henan, China

🇨🇳 #discoverChina with @cocoanext

📍Galápagos island, Ecuador

node.text:
Stunning photos of Montana’s nature 🍃 Which is your favourite?

Montana is filled with natural beauty. The state is also home to the Glacier National Park that boasts over 700 miles of trails, dotted with lakes, mountains and alpine meadows, so it might just be the perfect next adventure for hikers. ⛰️🇺🇸

Insider tip: As the park is quite big with so much to see, plan to stay at least 2-3 days to have enough time to enjoy its beauty.

📍Montana, United States

🇺🇸 #discoverUnited States with @kurtisminster

If you encounter a bear:⁣⁣
- Stay calm. If the bear sees you, talk in a low, calm voice and then regardless if it has seen you or not.⁣⁣
- Back up slowly. Never turn your back on a bear, or run. Running could trigger an attack.⁣⁣
- Do not stare. The bear will see a direct stare as a challenge.⁣⁣
- Give it space. Make sure it has a way to get away, and that you are not blocking access to a bear’s cubs or its food.⁣⁣

📍Alaska, United States

🇺🇸 #discoverUnitedStates
Video by @carasiciliano
